%, but with clear\nsystematic deviations. We argue that, as a consequence, fitting formulae based\non a universal form for the mass function may have limited utility in high\nprecision cosmological applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 May 2010 01:28:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 14 May 2010 05:28:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 28 May 2010 19:21:25 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 14 Mar 2011 20:39:39 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 17 Mar 2011 19:30:51 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Fri, 18 Mar 2011 19:46:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-19"}
